title: For Sale:  Vega Force Company Barrett M82A1 8mm NBB Gas Rifle - Collectors Item
location: San Luis Obispo County - Can travel to sell, California, United States
postcontent:
Vega Force Company Barrett M82A1 Non-Blowback Gas Rifle

Only 100 of the rifles were made by VFC before they went out of business, they are now a collectors item and only available from someone who already owns one.

Honestly the gun is horrible for field use, and is out-performed by even a lightly upgraded AEG, so as stated, this is a collectors item.

It is a remarkably well detailed and faithful recreation of the Barrett M82A1, real metal construction and precision welds put this baby together.  I had this thing sitting in a local gun/airsoft store for a while in an attempt to consign it, and people would come in all the time thinking this was a real Barrett M82A1, despite the entire muzzle break being blaze orange.

Only thing off with these is that the early generation models would have a tendency to blow out the o-ring at the valve that delivers the firing charge of gas, this one had that occur, I had a replacement o-ring sent, but never got the gun taken apart and the new one installed.  Considering this is a collectors item and crap for a field gun I will not be replacing the o-ring myself (at this things price tag it's better left to a professional) and I will not be marking down for non-firing status (seriously, its like a 25 cent o-ring).



*SERIOUS Buyers only/Disclaimer Section*
This section is reserved on all my listings for the "don't be stupid" section.  

First, I WILL NOT HAGGLE, the listed PRICE is 'THE' PRICE, and NO I DON'T WANT YOUR S****Y TRADE!.  I have calculated current market value for every item I have on here, what I paid for the items, condition on the item, and what extras I have thrown in to increase worth-while-ness to you the buyer.  My asking prices are more fair, and usually at least a couple to several hundred below market/what I paid.  I have taken very good care of my firearms.

Second, buyer will pay all fees.  I can't believe this has to be said here in CA, but its the number one question I get.  When you buy one from the store they don't pay your DROS for you! I will not either, again my prices are more than fair for what I'm selling.

Third, all transfers will happen at a public place, neutral ground if you will.  Firearms including blackpowder will be at an FFL/gun store(yes I know blackpowder won't DROS, the meet is for protection of both parties).  Airsoft items I have listed can be at any suitable location, Store, Play field, etc.  For items I list on consignment, I will direct you to the appropriate store.

Fourth, if you didn't figure it out from three, you need to be legally capable of owning the item and it will be transferred in accordance to applicable laws.  If you do a firearm transfer with me and your background check gets denied(which you should know if it will or not beforehand), then you had better find a new buyer, cause you're not getting a refund from me, idiot.

Finally, if you are a scammer, phisher or what not, you probably wont bother reading this this far.  But if you do, got straight to hell, do not pass go, do not collect $200.  My only means of contact from here is an e-mail I set up that I don't mind getting "burned" i.e. sold to companies, spammed, DDOS'ed, whatever.  You'll also be lucky to even get a reply from me if I think you are a scammer or wasting my time.  NO one on here will receive my phone number, address or an other contact info, you can have my name once we meet at the store, again, neutral ground, safe place for both parties.

If you are interested in an item let me know a time and suitable place(per 'Three') to meet upon first contact with me, or at least some proof that you're human, and actually in my area.  That's the best way to get a reply from me.  Stupid questions will be ignored.

title: Want To Buy:  WTB Rifle or Shotgun/please read description
postcontent:
This add has been edited from it's original form (In case you were wondering why it sounds familiar).

A month ago my girlfriend and I moved out of my parent's home with our 4 month old son. I come from a decent middle-class family and allowed my girlfriend to talk me into moving into a low income area, it was the worst decision of our lives. Gun shots can be heard every few days, fights in the cul-de-sac over who gave the mail man the best oral sex last night between the local women is a monthly occurrence, and every gas station owner in the area says they've been robbed at gunpoint at least twice.

I decided to go about posting this ad after some thug attempted to rob me at my car with a kitchen knife last Thursday night in a McDonald's parking lot. My girlfriend and I have tried a Maverick 88 at the range and the thing kicked her in the face and bruised my shoulder up pretty good, she refused to use it for any kind of defensive situation. We are now in search of preferably a semi-auto of both the rifle or shotgun variety to lessen the recoil, however, I will gladly consider any and all offers.

We're both 18 and we also only have about $200 dollars to spend, its the most we can save in a month and is quickly spent by the next month. If anyone would like to get rid of a rile or shotgun that's just collecting dust, is too small for you, won't sell for a reasonable price, or is just hurting your eyes to look at, I will buy it off of you if your willing to take $200 for it. I would prefer to meet during daylight hours in a public place and will show you proof of my age if needed. If you have any questions, I will gladly answer them.

title: For Sale:  300BLK brass cleaned and cut from converted from Lake City .223/556
postcontent:
Fellow Enthusiasts: We are currently in the process of converting 300BLK brass from Lake City .223/556.  

The conversion Process:

Brass is double struck using RCBS full length sizing dies.

Cases are then trimmed to size 1.355 +/- .003 (referenced from shoulder), chamfered and deburred using a RCBS hand trimmer.

Primer pocket hand swaged using a Hornady swagger.

Sonic cleaned and polished in dry media to ensure cases are thoroughly prepared (cleans inside, out and primer pockets of cases).

Cases are quality inspected every stage of conversion and additionally checked with a Wilson case gauge.

Brass is ready to be loaded with your choice of quality load!

The price is $.25 a piece. 

Available in quantities of no less than 100, bagged and triple checked for accuracy.

Current available quantities of once fired brass converted to high quality 300BLK cases for sale (Updated weekly):

Lake City  - 4000 pieces


You pay shipping based on your order. We use USPS Priority Mail Flat Rate Boxes, which arrive anywhere in the lower 48 states in around 3 days or less. We prefer discreet Paypal (Friends & Family), or USPS MO. 

*We can also process your .223/556 brass to 300BLK. Please contact us to discuss pricing based on your specs, location, and timetable.
